principal /ˈprɪnsɪpəl/

(principals) 

1. ADJ Principal means first in order of importance. 最重要的 [ADJ n] 

例： The principal reason for my change of mind is this. 我改变主意的最重要原因就是这个。 

例： ...the country's principal source of foreign exchange earnings. …该国最重要的外汇交易收入来源。 

2. N-COUNT The principal of a school is the person in charge of the school or college. 校长 

例： Donald King is the principal of Dartmouth High School. 唐纳德·金是达特茅斯中学的校长。 

3. N-COUNT The principal of a loan is the original amount of the loan, on which you pay interest. (贷款的) 本金 [商业] [usu sing]

